Text.Value: Stay with me. I'll get you out of here.
Then she told me to start running. She said when she catches me she's going to - to eat me too.
Silly silly, making promises you can't keep...
Slow down. First tell me what you're doing down here.
No, no, leave me alone!

EditorData.AnimationTags: [DG] Yenna limping towards the player while looking back, shouting.
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The player stops, confused, as Yenna comes running towards them out of the undercity shadows. She is bloodied and bruised, limping as though she'd been seriously hurt, shouting back into the darkness. In the distance, we hear a woman giggling. (Orin - emote recorded within Nested dialogue). It's terrifying.
EditorData.NodeContext: Shouting back at someone chasing her
EditorData.SFXTags: crazy woman giggeling in the background

Text.Value: A scary lady. She - she said her name was O-Orin.
She's coming. Oh please, please - don't let her take me!

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Another giggle. Louder. Closer. Yenna turn to look, terrified, then takes a step towards the player -

Text.Value: You'd stand by and let an innocent face my blades? Good.
Who's chasing you?
She - she found me and my cat Grub, snatched us off the streets and - and -
I won't let anything happen to you. I promise.
What would you do? Spill the blood of such an innocent? You'll get your chance.
No, I'm not. She's coming. Orin is coming!
Sounds like she's getting really close. Better start running...
She made me eat him.

EditorData.NodeContext: absolute horror/trauma - this was her beloved pet she ate

Text.Value: Please! You have to! O-Orin is coming for me.

EditorData.AnimationTags: [DG] Laezel (Orin) transforms into her true form.

Text.Value: Do not dare issue commands to me, whelp.
There was a lady. O-Orin.
Are you real? Is it really you? You have to help me - please!
Fleeing on the heels of a babe. I thought you were stronger than that.
What makes you think you're safer with me?
Why wouldn't I be real?
I - I thought you were her. O-Orin - the lady who took me. She can make herself look like anyone. She's a monster.
It's all right. You're safe now.

Synopsis: In certain areas in the Undercity, Orin will abduct and impersonate a target companion. Choice of target is the same as the camp abduction, but method and impersonation is not tied to the camp.
